                       St. Louis Post-Dispatch (Missouri)

                  July 7, 2000, Friday, FIVE STAR LIFT EDITION

BARNES-JEWISH RANKS NO. 8

SECTION: BUSINESS, Pg. C1

LENGTH: 113 words


For the eighth straight year, Barnes-Jewish Hospital in St. Louis is listed on
the honor roll of U.S. News & World Report's annual ranking of the best
hospitals in the United States.

Barnes-Jewish tied with Brigham and Women's Hospital in Boston for eighth place
in the rankings, which are to be released today. The rankings will be published
in the July 17 issue of the magazine.

No other area hospital made the honor roll, which includes 15 hospitals and is
based on physician surveys and medical data in various specialty fields.

Barnes-Jewish ranked fourth in the country in the area of respiratory disorders.
It ranked sixth in the area of kidney disease.

